igen Welteinbettung abgeschieden.  aWith media, an indirect relationship to the world (Weltverhältnis) is usually insinuated. This theoretical study, in contrast, reconstructs indirectness as an effect of medial reflexivity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aMass mediaxObjectivity. 0aMass mediaxPhilosophy. 4aDekonstruktion. 4aFundamentalontologie. 4aMediale Reflexivität. 4aMedien. 4aMedienphilosophie. 4aMedienwissenschaft. 4aNegative Dialektik. 4aNegative Medientheorie. 4aPhilosophie. 4aSystemtheorie. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aDeconstruction.  aFundamental Ontology.  aMedia Philosophy.  aMedia Studies.  aMedia.  aPhilosophy.  aSystems Theory.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript: Complete eBook-Package 2014z9783110401226oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/transcript.9783839428047zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839428047423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839428047/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-TGPb2014  aZDB-23-TGPc2014d2016